inn1.comm: oops, that will help England. Lee swings this a long way down the leg side, too far for Haddin to catch up with and it runs away for five wides. Still, swing there at least
better delivery this time, would be difficult not to be, outside off stump and Strauss leans forward to hang his bat inside the line
nudged, fiddled and nurdled off the pads towards midwicket. Still a touch of swing for Lee
no swing from this length - too short - but the line is impeccable and Strauss stands tall to defend
shortish again, this time the line is wider, and Strauss, unusually for him, mistimes a cut shot. Earns a single wide of cover to bring Prior on strike against Lee
Prior is away! Easy as you like. Gets a leg-stump half-volley and clips it neatly to the square leg boundary
Lee adjusts his line to outside off stump and Prior lifts his bat high out of harm's way
races in as always and starts well - up and around off stump - Strauss drives without much timing, wide of mid-off for a jogged single

ooh, this is through Prior but somehow misses everything! It was full and swung back in late, Prior looked like he wanted to leave but then suddenly saw it swing back and tried to squeeze out a defence. It went through the gate and just about missed off stump
big swing again this time, Prior aims a defence and it slides off the inside-edge, trickling out to midwicket for a well-run couple
no swing this time so Prior's leave alone outside off occurs with no alarms
ah, lovely stuff. Full, wide half-volley asking to be dispatched and Prior loves a drive. He leant into it beautifully and stroked it to the cover rope
steered backwards of square on the off side where it's smartly fielded
strangled appeal as Strauss inside-edges a loose drive into his pads. Good delivery, nipped back from a full length
whoosh, bit of a flat-foot swish outside off. Not a great shot but it excited Lee enough to have a chirp. Strauss is utterly unmoved as always
back of a length this time and Strauss solidly blocks back at the bowler
flash and four! Not entirely middled but Strauss really threw his arms at it and it cleared point and sped to the boundary

that's all for Strauss, Lee gets his man! Another flat-footed swipe outside off stump, finds a thickish edge that Haddin gleefully collects. It was short and wide but not for the first time today Strauss missed the cut shot he normally nails
Trott is away in classic Trott fashion, shuffling across his stumps to quietly work the ball off his legs towards midwicket
Bollinger digs in a short ball that Prior turns this around the corner to the short fine leg fielder
decent bounce for Bollinger from back of the length and Prior blocks to cover
enough width for Prior to throw his arms, very flowing drive, but straight to cover
Prior is again sturdy in defence
good lengths and lines from Bollinger and Prior turns his wrists over the ball to send it to midwicket
Bollinger hangs the ball around off stump and Trott blocks before continuing with his main reason for being out there - marking his guard
pitch looks very good for runs, ball coming onto the bat, enough bounce. Prior celebrates all of this by defending
hint of edge here, half-steered-half-outside-edge, runs away to third man
more solid defence as Lee continues to hammer away on an excellent line and length
touch fuller and it's played firmly to deep cover
Lee sears in a yorker, full and straight and Prior jabs it away just in time. 94mph according to the speedgun
Prior looks in good touch, driving elegantly and on the up, wide of mid-off and speeds to the boundary
Bollinger bangs in a short ball, rather that stand tall and thwack it over third man, Trott eases out the way of it. Good choice I suspect
much fuller this time and despite it being outside off stump, Trott works it to leg
good line from Bollinger, very straight, good length too. Trott can do nothing but defend
Trott does play this on the off side, driving without much timing to mid-off
Bollinger giving Trott no width at all and from back of a length Trott has no option but to defend
this time there is a hint of width which allows Trott to dab a single to third man
Trott on the go straight away, skipping down the wicket and aiming a whip to leg. Doesn't get any of it and is rewarded with a tirade from Haddin behind the stumps. Pleasant lad, that Haddin
Trott again can't get this away as Watson's line is too good
Trott shuffled to the leg side this time - which is odd. Gives himself enough room to work to third man
Prior has looked typically busy and nudes a single to mid-on
this will frustrate Trott. Gets his beloved leg-stump line but clips it straight to short midwicket
Watson gives him a second opportunity and this time Trott makes no mistake, flicking it finer and it runs away to the square leg rope, beating the deep midwicket fielder
wow, shades of Haddin here as Prior gets down the wicket and gives himself room outside leg to smash this over mid-off and it lands just inside the rope
four more! Nicely done from Prior, gets his the room outside off that is his lifeblood, and thumps it through cover
Bollinger's response is to bang it in short and Prior mistimes a pull, comes high off the bat and trickles to midwicket
too full from Bollinger, and Trott times his off-side push ideally and the ball seems to gather pace on its way to the rope
Bollinger returns to a good length and line and Trott dabs a single behind square on the off side
good slower ball beats Prior outside off
wrong line again from Watson, bowling on Trott's pads with fine leg up makes no sense and Trott's flick beats the man and runs away to the boundary
better line, outside off stump and Trott aims a drive, slicing it and losing his bottom hand off the bat as he plays it. Finds a gap at cover
again Watson explores Trott's pads and is predictably worked away through midwicket
touch too straight from Watson and Prior mistimes a drive down the ground
a hint of room outside off allows Trott to jab to third man
Watson finishes the over much better than he started it, landing it on a fuller length and off stump
starts fullish around off stump - tidy - and it's pushed to cover
touch slower from Hastings and it's driven firmly back at the bowler, smashing into his shins
Trott picks out mid-on from a ball that lands well outside off

ooh, almost another run out farce for England! Trott dabbed it to where a second slip could have been, Prior motored up for a single and Trott took a long time to get going, Haddin threw in but Trott got himself in the way and it thudded off his back
Prior gets down on one knee and sweeps, risky shot, picked out short fine leg who misfields and allows a couple
this time it's pushed firmly to cover
Watson lands a straight ball that Trott tries to whip to leg but misses
little bit short and a little bit wide and the cut shot finds point
Trott flicks rather expansively but only for single to fine leg
wrong line from Watson around leg stump, Prior tries to whip it but gets more edge than middle
again Watson is on the pads, desperate not to give Prior width outside off - Prior works it with his wrists to leg
good offcutter around off stump and Trott clamps down to run it to third man
ooh, Prior tries to work to third man but the slower ball means it's a bottom edge that bounces over the stumps and Haddin's head
Trott gives himself room and mistimes a drive to cover
with soft hands it's worked to square leg. Just singles available at the moment
hint of width allows Trott to flow a drive but straight to cover
Hastings is sliding the ball in nicely, not giving Trott any room and the attempted work-to-third-man is inside-edged
pushed straight to cover again
'Welcome back,' says Prior, charging down the track and cracking a short of length ball over mid-off for four
a swinging full ball at 146kph is the response from Lee, Prior digs it out towards cover
length ball at 144kph, Trott tucks it towards midwicket and scampers a single
Lee fires in a yorker on offstump,  blocked to the off side
shorter this time from Lee, defended solidly by Prior
a high full toss well outside off, clocked at 148kph, slapped towards sweeper cover by Prior for a couple
short and well outside off, chopped towards deep point by Trott
keeps it way outside off, attempted slower ball, full delivery, mistimed by Prior back to the bowler
nothing wrong with the timing on that one, width offered and Prior slashes that over cover for four
clips this one from offstump towards midwicket for a quick single
another easy single as the ball is worked towards point
Hastings keeps it steady, length ball on off, punched back towards the bowler, Haddin screams 'Down' as soon as the shot is played, Hastings gets down to field that
Lee nearly hits 150kph, that was 149.9, length ball just outside off, pushed towards down the ground

good god! what a mess that was, terrible cricket all around, both batsmen find themselves at the same end after a huge mix-up, Australia still manage to not get the run-out, Trott blocks the ball from Lee and he's not sure where that went, he turns round to see it round in front of middle stump and has his back to the non-striker as the ball nestles between middle and off stump after rolling gently back, Prior was charging down the track, no idea why he was, Lee races towards the ball, collides with Trott at the batsman's crease, and bowler, batsman and non-striker were all at the striker's end, Lee manages to get the ball after a couple of collisions with Trott, he has loads of time to throw the ball to the other end and get the run-out, he fires in the throw wide though and the fielder at the non-striker's end couldn't collect it and Trott heaves a sigh of relief, as does Prior
whoah, what a shot that is, Prior absolutely wallops that slightly short one over midwicket, Lee can't be feeling too happy right now
full ball played past extra cover
nudged toward square leg for a single
slower ball outside off, worked to third man
defended confidently on the front foot
Trott defends on the off, takes two steps forward for the run and then says "No no no no no"
defended on the off side once again
quicker through the air on the pads, Trott works the ball behind square
Prior tries to drive but it's a loose shot and the ball takes the outside edge towards short third man
quicker ball again, defended on the leg side
good length around off stump, played towards the leg side
wide ball down leg side, Haddin can't collect that, far too wide
nudged on the off side off the back foot
good length but there's width outside off stump, allowing the batsman space to cut towards third man
Trott moves forward and across to work the ball off his pads towards midwicket, Watson dives and makes a sharp save
slower ball outside off stump at 105 kph, Trott tries to force through cover but mis-times it
driven through cover this time for the single
Trott waits for the flighted delivery around off and drives powerfully through cover. Lee sprints to his right along the boundary and dives full length to save the four
Trott sweeps but doesn't make contact. Doherty appeals for leg before. Unsuccessfully.
Played through square leg for one
Prior attempts to sweep from outside off and gets an inside edge on to the pad
punched off the back foot towards mid-on but the fielder from midwicket cuts it off
cut off the back foot through point
good length around off stump, Prior moves back and across and pulls towards mid-on
Prior waits on this one and guides it towards third man
good length, angling into off stump, worked off the pads but Watson's sharp at midwicket
White has to run a long way to his right on the cover boundary to cut off Trott's fluent drive off the front foot
a bit of swing into the right-hander, Trott inside-edges it towards square leg and sets off. He gets sent back
can't hit that one. In the blockhole. Defended.
Prior misses the sweep but that's because Doherty was down leg side
driven fluently but straight to the man at cover
Prior makes room by moving towards leg, he's trying to go inside out over the infield. Edged towards short third man
pushed on the off for a single. Trott once again gets between the throw from Clarke and the stumps and cops a blow.
driven into the deep for two this time
nudged watchfully off the front foot towards the off side for one
worked off the pads on the front foot through square leg
that's a touch too short and Prior is quick to move back and cut the ball hard. He hit that in the air but wide of the fielder at point
again it's a bit short and Prior slaps the ball through cover point off the back foot
fuller and wider this time. Trott reaches out and drives to deep cover
tossed up into the blockhole, Trott plays it back to the bowler
driven to long-on for a single
Doherty angles the ball into Trott who drives fluently to long off
the length is short outside off, Prior cuts in front of point for one
Trott strides forward and defends back towards the bowler
Trott gets to 50 off 65 balls by driving a wide ball through cover point
driven hard, but to the fielder at cover
quicker and straighter ball, Prior cuts from off stump through the off side

caught! Prior's cut one straight to point. The length was good and the line was outside off. Prior went back into his crease to cut, and found Doherty. That spun and bounced a touch and it hit the top edge
Pietersen defends the first ball towards the bowler
played towards midwicket for one
defended once again on the leg side
Trott turns the strike over once again with a deft single towards the leg side
Pietersen takes a step out and punches the ball towards long off
and Pietersen attempts to drive past the fielder at mid-on. Bollinger does well to dive to his left and take the pace off the ball
and here he goes! Lofting the ball into the vacant space at the long-on boundary. Pietersen came down and hit it cleanly
defended on the front foot towards the off
played off the back foot towards point
Trott takes a stride forward and blocks
nudged off the front foot towards midwicket for one
defended on the back foot towards the off
Trott inside edges a drive on to his pad and the ball goes on the off
a quick full toss and Trott hits it back to the bowler on the bounce
a slower, flighted delivery. Trott drives through cover for one
Pietersen got into position for the sweep early and paddled it to fine leg
Trott jumps out, gets to the pitch of the ball and drives straight past the bowler
Pietersen takes two steps down and then defends
he stays back this time and steers the ball through point
Trott goes back and across and flicks a straight one through square leg
Pietersen gets down on one knee for the paddle sweep very early once again, and collects one
defended towards midwicket on the back foot
Trott makes room to drive and forces Lee to sprint along the boundary rope to save four at deep cover
Pietersen comes down the pitch and gets hit on the pad. Smith appeals but he was a long way forward and perhaps outside the line.
played towards cover point for a single

caught at long-on! The fielder was back on the boundary this time, but Pietersen went after Smith anyway. He came forward, got under the ball and hoisted it towards the boundary. Not enough distance on it though and Marsh ran in a few paces to take a simple catch
Bell steps out right away and punches to mid-off

and he's been caught as well! Bell took two steps out of his crease to play the ball, Smith beat him in the flight and the ball pitched short of the batsman, Bell tried to readjust to dab the ball towards the off side but got a thick edge through to Haddin. Haddin almost wanted to complete the stumping as well, before realizing that Bell had edged it.
Morgan plays his first ball back to the bowler
quicker ball and dead straight. Defended on the back foot on the leg side
Trott misses the sweep and the ball hits the pad. Doherty appeals for lbw and is turned down. Clarke has a word about the review but decides against it.
defended on the off side from the crease
played back to the bowler
cut off the back foot towards point
punched off the back foot towards cover for a quick single. Just one run off that over.
nudged behind point for another quick single
a bit too short, allowing Morgan to go back and slap the ball towards mid-off
driven off the back foot past midwicket for a single
Morgan moves forward and across to nudge the ball off the pads towards square leg
full toss and Trott sweeps towards deep square leg
the faster one from Smith and Trott defends from his crease towards the bowler
Morgan tries to reverse sweep and there's a slip in place. The ball goes to the fielder on the bounce.

Morgan tries to defend on the front foot and gets hit on the pad. Haddin collects the ball and underarms it towards the non-striker's end and concedes an overthrow. Doherty wasn't anticipating the ball coming towards him.
defended on the front foot
played through the off side for a single
Morgan works the ball from middle and leg towards the on side
Morgan plays a pre-meditated paddle sweep and collects two
good length outside off, Trott strides forward and drives towards cover
Lee gets that one to swing back into Trott. The length was full and Trott worked the ball through midwicket
too wide from Lee and Trott reaches out to tap it to the fielder on the point boundary
Morgan drives a full ball through point and gives the fielder at third man some running to do
pushed off the front foot towards the off side
Lee slants the ball into the left-hander from round the wicket. Morgan works the ball past midwicket but the fielder at mid-on runs to his left and cuts it off
Trott comes forward and pushes the ball off his pads through the leg side
Morgan also guides the ball through square leg
Doherty fires the ball into the pads, Trott can't make contact with the sweep
driven to long off for a single
width offered outside off and Morgan cuts through point off the back foot
Trott steps out and closes the face to play the ball towards midwicket
played towards cover on the front foot
a flatter shorter delivery and Trott cuts towards the fielder on the point boundary
nudged off the front foot towards the off for a quick single
he's hit that superbly. The length was full, Trott got down on one knee and slog-swept the ball firmly towards the deep midwicket boundary. First four for him in 24 overs.
now he gives Morgan the strike with a single
Morgan reaches out for a wide one and drives through the off side
played back to the bowler
too full to cut and Morgan mis-times the shot through point
defended on the front foot towards the off side
Doherty bowls quicker and faster, Trott was down the pitch and adjusted his shot and played the ball towards deep square
worked off the pads through midwicket
cut off the back foot towards deep point. That's the end of Doherty's spell. He's done a good job considering he began bowling when Prior was batting aggressively.
starts outside off stump on a length and Morgan steers a pat to cover
back of a length again from Bollinger, Trott shuffles outside off to work to midwicket
Bollinger finds an ideal off-stump line and Morgan gets everything behind his block
Morgan hasn't looked at his best this series but his back-foot drive here really pings to cover
cracker from Bollinger! Back of a length and the harder new ball zips away and climbs past the outside edge
touch slower this time and the line remains impeccable, hugging off stump. Morgan defends to end a fine Bollinger over
Trott is down the wicket to greet Hastings and slapping a drive past mid-off, all along the ground to the boundary
that keeps Trott in his crease and from there he works an ugly drive to long-off
Hastings slips this down the leg side but it flicks the pads on its way through to Haddin
Hastings again explores the pads and Morgan flicks a single to square leg to bring the 200 up
full and outside off stump, Trott drags it back to the bowler
poor line this time, sliding down leg and Trott clips it around the corner
Morgan skips down the wicket at Bollinger, who bangs it in short in response, Morgan then guides an uppish cut to third man
Bollinger's good line means Trott can only open the face to third man
ooh, Bollinger bangs in a short ball that Morgan tries to pull. Didn't get anything of it and it spooned just over midwicket
Trott dabs another single to third man, giving himself a bit of room to play the shot
Hussey fields very smartly at midwicket, saving Morgan's well-timed flick and the batsmen scamper through
after giving himself room outside leg this time Trott reverts to his more customary move, outside off, and working to midwicket to bring up the 50 stand
Trott gives himself room outside leg again to carve Hastings out to deep point
ah, lovely shot. Don't bowl on Trott's pads. It's a lesson Australians have refused to learn all tour. Flicked around the corner with perfect timing to bring up a boundary away from a hundred
much better line from Hastings outside off and it's jabbed to third man
short ball and whipped, half-pull, out to deep midwicket. Just a single away...

there is Trott's hundred and fittingly gets there by working a full ball to deep midwicket. After searching for it, he eventually kisses the England  badge on his helmet. Excellent innings really, absolutely no fuss at all
poor ball, very short and down the leg side. Morgan gives this absolutely everything in his pull shot and it sails high to the fine leg rope
fullish ball is pushed to cover for a scampered single
Morgan crouches low in his stance and stays low as he chops this to deep point
full and wide of off stump, Trott looked to chase the drive but couldn't quite reach it
good line and length from Bollinger and solidly blocked to point
oops, full toss that seems to surprise Trott. It was quite a high full toss and Trott couldn't take advantage, mistiming to mid-off
better timing on this drive but mid-off is back allowing a single. Time for the Powerplay methinks
starts well enough outside off and is poked to third man
fuller ball is driven firmly back at him
Trott is not a fashionable bloke but tries to prove just how cool he is by reverse sweeping here. Doesn't get much of it

Hussey gets the breakthrough! Plenty of turn here for him, comes in a long way and cramped Trott as he tried to cut, took the bottom edge and cannoned onto middle stump. Excellent breakthrough to end a fine innings
Collingwood is the new man and does something he failed to last game - finds the middle of the bat - but only to steer to point
end of an excellent over, Collingwood leans forward and prods to mid-off
starts well enough on a length around middle and poked away in defence
this time Collingwood is solidly forward in defence
driven this time but straight to cover. Good start from Smith
finally Collingwood gets off the strike, working a single into space
Morgan flicks finely around the corner to pick off a single
Collingwood's back-foot bunt goes straight to mid-off

Hussey gets his second! Morgan's reverse-sweep was timed well but straight to point, who jumped high to take the chance above his head. Wickets falling at ideal time and England are in danger of having the tail in for the Powerplay
Yardy plonks his first ball through mid-off for a single
Collingwood's attempted drive slides off the thickish edge to point
worked to mid-on, Collingwood keeps finding the infield
this time Collingwood does find the single, pushing down the ground
Yardy gets a straight ball that is defended very, very carefully
starts well on off stump and Collingwood dabs a single to third man
very full from Lee, good line too and Yardy can only squeeze a single to third man
full and swinging in, fine delivery, Collingwood can only just about dig it out
Collingwood down the wicket, bounding down, and drives solidly but straight to deep cover
some late inswing takes this towards Yard's pads and he flicks towards fine leg where Cameron white scoots around and slides to field
full again, excellent over really, and Yardy can only bunt to cover
good start from Bollinger, haring in and landing it on a length, worked to midwicket
too short from Bollinger, width too, Yardy upper-cuts with enough top edge to beat the sliding fielder at third man
fuller this time, much better, and it thuds off the pads
Collingwood bounds down the wicket again and heaves across the line, no great timing but the intent is right and he gets a couple to deep midwicket
Collingwood is again down the wicket but Bollinger adjusts well and prods a single to cover
Yardy gets down very early to try and dab a poke sweep, crashes into the ribs and Bollinger, oddly, appeals
heave ho! There we go! Collingwood has finally middled one and he's absolutely mullered it. Down the wicket and slugged into the stands over midwicket
this time it's wide outside off and Collingwood works to third man
slower bouncer and Yardy has to wait and wait to slog this to midwicket
Yardy gives himself room outside leg and tries to carve it away, goes too far though and can't reach it
ugly, but it does the trick. Yardy again giving himself plenty of room and the carve is toe-ended past the keeper to the third man rope
full toss on the pads and Yardy wheels it towards deep square
this Yardy innings is beginning to flow. Bollinger lands just short of a good length and Yardy is deep  into his crease to shove it to the midwicket rope, timed it well
cut firmly but straight to point. Collingwood wants one but is rightly sent back
Yardy stepped back and Bollinger responded but going full, but overcooked it and a full toss was slapped straight of deep midwicket for four
this time it's worked with a bit of edge into the off side
ah, Collingwood middles another! Plays this really well. Down the wicket and eased, rather than slugged, to the long-on boundary
Bollinger is struggling this over, and shoves this a long, long way outside off stump
good ball to finish a poor over. Collingwood down the wicket and Bollinger dug in a slower bouncer that the batsman couldn't work into the leg side
Yardy down the wicket and throwing his arms at the ball, doesn't time it at all and it trickles to cover. England though about a single but there was none there
good full length here, slower too, and difficult to get away. Driven without much timing to long-off
Collingwood again advances before trying to sweep/ramp it over short midwicket, the slower ball meant he was through it long before it arrived

charging down the track again and Collingwood tried to heave to leg. Missed and it struck him on the pads. Clarke calls for a review because it hit on the back leg, but outside off stump so never going to be at
another appeal from Watson as a fullish ball gets Yardy on the pads as he tried to flick around the corner
another slower ball the Collingwood slaps without much timing to deep mid-on
Collingwood lines up a sweep, smashes it hard straight to deep midwicket on the bounce. White makes an utter hash of the save and it goes through him to the rope
attempted reverse-poke comes off a flurry of bat and glove and trickles for one
Yardy gives himself room to smack to cover for a swift single
Collingwood shelves the reverse sweep and pushes to long-off, comes back for the second and would have been gone if it hit but it didn't
fired in full and straight and bunted back to the bowler

Collingwood tries to repeat the sweep/heave that got the boundary earlier, this time he timed it too well and it went straight to White who made no mistake this time. Ends an ugly innings but at least it showed signs of form
short ball from Watson, Shahzad gives himself room to wristily flick to past point
this time Shahzad walks across his stumps but Watson follows and it's driven to cover
another wristy drive but it slides off the edge past Haddin
Yardy down on one knee trying to poke a sweep fine but gets too much of it and it goes to fine leg
flicked airily, but straight to mid-on
Yardy's lack of timing saves him here as the drive goes one-bounce to deepish mid-off
excellent shot from Yardy, really top stuff. Down the wicket and giving himself room to drive into a gap wide of long-off for four. This is turning into an unlikely gem of an innings
this is horridly timed down the ground, trickling to long-on
Hussey gets another! What figures he has. Shahzad mistimes a full toss and it loops to midwicket who takes a very gentle chance
Yardy is down the wicket, giving himself some room and drives excellently down the ground and times it well enough to run for four
this is shoved in very short and Yardy should have got more, in the end he belted a pull shot to deep midwicket. Leaves Tremlett to try and bring up the 300
good finish to an excellent spell from Hussey, shoved in quick and full and past Tremlett's attempted drive

inn2.comm: Steered towards third man for a single
good length around off stump, Haddin stays in his crease and defends
Haddin gets squared up a touch as he attempts to defend from the crease, that ball swung away a touch from the right-hander. Single towards cover
defended on the back foot towards the bowler
Anderson angles into Watson's body and he nudges towards the leg side for a quick one
Haddin tries to make room by moving towards leg but Anderson follows him and cramps him up. Haddin ends up defending on the off side
Shahzad hits a good length and slants the ball into Watson who gets behind the line and blocks
Watson strides forward and drives towards extra cover
good length just outside off, pushed off the front foot towards the off side
Watson strides forward and punches a good length ball towards mid-off
good length but the line is just outside off, Watson chops it towards third man
Haddin gets a thick inside edge as he tries to drive and the ball races away through midwicket, Morgan pursues and pulls it in just inside the boundary
slants down leg side and Watson misses the glance
defended on the front foot

top effort from Morgan! Watson clipped a full ball off his pads in the air and it travelled fast towards deep midwicket. Morgan came in running from the boundary to take the flat catch but the ball fell short of him and bounced past
defended on the back foot
dabbed towards the off side, Haddin wanted a risky single and he would have been history had Collingwood hit the stumps from point
pushed towards the off side
good length outside off stump, Watson cuts but mis-times the shot towards point, 140.3kph that was
cut, and it is timed well, but the placement is straight to the fielder
worked off the hips through midwicket for a single
Haddin makes room again by moving towards leg. He tries to flay the ball over the off side but he had moved so far away that he couldn't reach it
pushed off the back foot towards point
makes room and smash! Haddin goes inside out and lofts the ball over mid-off for four. Clean, crisp contact to a length delivery
driven firmly off the front foot towards extra cover. The fielder there can't stop it cleanly so there's a single available
and Haddin does it again. Length delivery outside off stump. Haddin moves outside leg and lifts the ball over mid-off for another inside-out four
short and wide outside off, Haddin makes a bit of room - not as much as previous times - but absolutely blazes it through point with a fierce cut shot
Anderson darts one into the pads and the ball hits the pad as Haddin gets squared up in his crease. Watson calls him for a single after the ball goes towards third man
defended solidly off the front foot
defended on the front foot once again
good length ball and this time Haddin moves a touch towards the off and swings the ball wide of the fielder at short fine leg. He didn't middle that - more of an inside edge - but he will take it
defended on the back foot towards the off
Haddin winds up and has a hard swing at a good length delivery. He gets a thick inside edge on to his thigh

caught! Haddin has spooned one to cover. It was the slower one from Tremlett and it nipped into Haddin, who was early on the drive. He went hard at the ball and hit it at a nice, easy height to Strauss at cover
full ball on leg stump, Marsh leans across and nudges it towards the on-side for one
Watson stays solid in defence and plays from the crease
hits Marsh on the pad with one that slants into the left-hander. The impact was on top of the pad so maybe a bit too high.
Marsh moves forward and plays the ball with the angle into him towards the leg side
no room for Marsh to work with whatsoever with this angle into him, he pushes on the off side

caught and bowled! Anderson was testing Marsh with this angle into the left-hander from round the wicket. He was attacking the stumps constantly and not giving the batsman room. Marsh pushed a bit more at this one, the ball hit the bat a little low and went straight back to the bowler. Caught and bowled chances are rarely easy, but this one was.
Clarke defends his first ball on the back foot
Watson hasn't had much of the strike of late and he rotates it with a drive off the front foot towards cover
left alone outside off stump
good length outside off stump, Clarke strides forward and lets it go again
and another one goes past under the watchful eyes of Michael Clarke, don't see too many batsmen leaving three out of four deliveries these days
this time the line is closer to the body and Clarke defends
driven off the front foot towards mid-off
tight line and length from Anderson on off and middle. Watson gets behind it and defends from his crease
too full and too straight this time and Watson clips the ball off his pads through midwicket
good length on off stump, Clarke strides forward and plays the ball towards point
the length is a touch shorter and Clarke was forward as the ball rose on him. He got on top of the bounce by jumping before punching the ball through cover
defended on the off side
the length is on the shorter side and Watson plays that flowing muscular pull shot of his, there's a man on the boundary at deep midwicket though
played with an open face off the back foot towards point
Tremlett strays on to the pads and Watson gives it a real whip with his wrists to send the ball racing towards deep backward square
he doesn't time the straight drive well though, but he's placed it straight enough to get one before mid-off and mid-on converge on the ball
Clarke moves forward and plays a punchy drive, but hits the ball on the bounce to the fielder at short cover
Clarke moves across his stumps and dabs the ball close on the leg side for a single
there's width outside the off stump on offer and Watson cuts the ball firmly to third man
full ball on off stump, Clarke drives off the front foot towards mid-off
Clarke drives off the front foot towards cover point, can't find the gap though
too straight from Shahzad and Clarke flicks through midwicket
length delivery outside off stump. It may have been a bit slower too. Watson plants his foot forward, winds up, and biffs the ball over the fielder at mid-on for four
over mid-off this time. Both the fielders at mid-on and mid-off are in the circle and Watson backed himself to hit cleanly over them.
both those fielders are back on the boundary now so Watson drives straight but along the ground
defended confidently on the front foot towards the off side

massive hit! Watson has such power and yet he looks so smooth and efficient when he makes clean contact. Length delivery outside off and Watson swings across the line to send the ball into the stands at the long-on boundary
full toss and Watson punches it down the ground for one
good length outside off. Clarke lets it go.
full and straight, Clarke flicks off the pads to midwicket
Tremlett strays on to the pads and Clarke moves across and glances the ball off his hips towards the fine-leg boundary. Nothing fancy, text-book leg glance.
good length on off stump, Watson defends towards point. Clarke comes quite a long way down from the non-striker's end before he has to hurry back
Watson aimed for the swing across the line but Collingwood is slower and he was through the shot too early and missed
pushed down the ground with a straight bat towards long on
too straight and Clarke uses the angle to move across and flick through midwicket
too wide outside off and Watson uses the freedom to glide the ball between short third man and point with a well-timed cut
was he aiming for the mow there? Watson brought his bat down in a hurry and opened the face to dab the ball towards point in the end
worked through square leg for one
Watson goes back and nudges the ball gently towards midwicket. the fielder needs to come off the boundary so they sprint two
Clarke nudges the ball towards square leg for another quick single
Watson tried to force that through the off side but mis-timed it towards mid-off
pushed towards mid-on for a single
width outside off stump, met with a flat-batted cut out to deep point
less width this time, and dabbed into the covers with a defensive bat
drawn forward, and blocked to mid-off
chopped hard out to backward point
a hint of outswing, but starting too wide. Driven into the gap at cover
open-faced steer, down to third man
brought forward, half an appeal
blocked once again
good loopy delivery, drops onto a good length, and defended
round the wicket, a bit of angle onto leg stump, and worked round the corner
picks the gap again, but Yardy's in a good rhythm
drawn down the track but a touch beaten in flight. Decent over
forward to a good-length nibbler, and defended
looped onto a middle-and-off-stump line. Pushed firmly back to the bowler
back a touch in length, defended again
good line and length from Collingwood, the ball nips off the seam a touch and deflects to square leg
driven from deep in the crease, picked up at midwicket
cracking delivery! That one burst off the seam, nipped through the gate, and flicked the top of middle stump! Great stuff from Colly, who is justifying his place in the side once again ...
cut firmly in front of square, and there is Watto's fifty. Great effort once again
tossed onto a good length from around the wicket, and blocked
a monstrous mow into no-man's land at deep cover. A bit lucky, but gets away with it
looped onto leg stump, and pushed to mid-on
dragged down, a bit of a rank delivery to be frank, but met with a calm nudge off the pads
slow, slow, slow delivery, a fraction short, but not enough pace to work with. A miscued pull dribbles out to mid-on
good areas from Colly, shaping into the batsman and pushed down the ground
defended from the crease, and this one is jabbed back down the pitch, in a bit of a hurry
another single down the ground, excellent rhythm from Collingwood
more subtle movement through to the air, and defended again
pushed out to mid-on, and well fielded with a stretch. On the spot again
massive appeal as this one jags off the seam, but there looked as though there was bat involved there, and it might have been down leg. Otherwise, pretty close
prodded into the covers
poor ball, but the leg-side sweeper is in place to tidy up a long-hop
poked into the covers, and easily fielded
fuller delivery, and this one is lofted into space over mid-on. Plugs as it lands, and they jog back for two
fuller, and straighter. Defended
really wide on the crease, ends up as a low full-toss, and Prior can't do much as the ball is nutmegged between his legs. Looked as though there was bat involved, but the umpire thinks not
driven up to cover
driven through mid-on
good delivery, a fraction shorter but arrow-straight. White prods down at the last minute
more appreciable nibble off the seam, and blocked once again
blatted into the covers, where Strauss fields with a juggle
defended with a shuffle on off stump. Excellent probing work from Collingwood. He's bowling like Ronnie Irani in 2002. And that's actually a compliment
a swishing drive, back down the track but intercepted in Shahzad's followthrough
too much width, and clobbered out to deep point. A sniff of reverse swing though ...
more slight movement, open-faced guide to point
defended off the back foot, a quick call, and through they hustle
wide on the crease, angling in and defended with a big stride
genuine swing that time, very full and a bit too wide, but White's wild swing finds nothing but thin air
great shape from Collingwood, swinging late and defended on middle-and-leg
this one stays straight, and is calmly driven to mid-off
driven hard, but straight into the turf, Collingwood leaps in his followthrough and intercepts
speared into the toes, swinging all the way, and shovelled into the leg-side
on the pads, clipped firmly
swinging late, and way down leg
outside off, pushed into the covers. Another tidy over
swished across the line from outside off, but can't get enough pace on the shot as mid-on fields
clear swing, angling from outside off towards middle. Met with a mow, and picked up at midwicket. That came right off the toe
outswinger this time, good variation. Nudged down to third man
banged in short, decent delivery, pulled to the midwicket sweeper
driven, in the air, but that beats the diving mid-off, and it's a very welcome boundary. They've been few and far between in recent overs
massive wicket! Too wide to take on, and Watson's airy swish takes a thin top edge to Prior. Now England are in the driving seat
blocked into the covers
good nip off the seam again, deflected square with one hand coming off the bat
jags off the pitch again, another single to midwicket
defended once again, this really is a fine spell
a fraction shorter but swished straight to midwicket
dabbed down to third man, another single. And that's the halfway mark of the innings
this is slashed wide of point down to the boundary rider who scoots round to save
Shahzad finds a straighter line is rewarded with a rare straight bat from White, who has played possibly the ugliest 27 balls I've ever seen. And I've watched plenty of Collingwood
urgh, this is once again filthy looking from White, but effective enough as it's slugged wide of long-off
back on careful defence here
Shahzad dares fuller, looking for swing and it's carefully blocked out. Shahzad spins on his heels and swaggers back to his mark
big wind up from Shahzad as he was about to deliver, but it was all a deception because it's in fact slower, much slower and blocked away
Collingwood wobbles this onto a straight line and length and Hussey has no pace to work this into space
touch fuller and a leg-stump line means Hussey can tuck it away to the leg side
White backs away looking for room, Colly in the manner of Courtney Walsh, sort of, follows him so White has to fiddle it around the corner
this time White does succeed in giving himself room and carves out to deep cover
a firm drive is played so perfectly straight that it went into the stumps at the non-striker's end
a Collingwood slower ball is very slow and Hussey has to do all the work to get drive, earning a single to a deepish mid-off

starts with a pretty meek half-tracker that is pulled smartly, in front of midwicket where... OH NO! Silly KP slid to field with one hand, flicked it up but onto his own body and it bounced off over the rope. Oops
after all that fun this is worked away into space for one
the batsmen trade singles as White pushes this into the off side
this is on a length around off stump but Hussey's steer picks out the infielder at point
fuller from Tremlett, which always seems hazardous, but the firm drive finds a tumbling Bell
this is full again and driven with a hint of inside edge towards mid-off
starts slow around middle and is fiddled to leg
Trott has found a decent enough line sliding into the batsman and thuds off the thigh towards square leg
the lack of pace means the midwicket-clip is not firm enough

White has seen enough and goes for a booming drive down the ground, not perfectly timed and Luke Wright slid brilliantly to pull off a remarkable save on the long-off boundary. He really is a special(ist) fielder
driven hard again but straight to cover
ooh, Trott almost has a breakthrough. Backs away to give himself room and aims a carve over cover that gets a top edge which loops over the infield and plops down safely
cracker from Tremlett. Beats White in all sorts of ways. Bounced, was a touch quicker and jagged away off the seam past a hanging defensive prod
beaten again! This was a less special delivery, touch wide and White aimed a late cut and it skimmed past the edge
shortish ball is crashed to short extra cover where Bell fields superbly
close again, on and around off stump and the attempted smash to leg comes off an inside edge
firmly driven from the crease but to mid-off
Tremlett ends a good over by landing this back of a length on off stump and it skews off an inside edge again
Trott lands this on a length around middle and again the inside edge is productive, earning a couple to square leg
fiddled into the leg side for a jogged single
White tries to give himself room but Trott follows him and the slap to off isn't timed at all
full ball meets a very full face that sends the ball to long-on
driven again safely, but Australia need some boundaries
this is hit hard down to KP on the cover boundary who makes no mistake cutting the ball off
starts a touch short and is pulled hard but straight to deep midwicket
White gets down low to dip this over his head, he then gets his head down and motors three
touch shorter and Hussey gets deep into his crease to push to long-off
aah, missed stumping, White charged down and Yardy fired it in much quicker and wide, beat White, and Prior spilled a certain stumping chance
this is driven firmly back down the wicket
waa? Moon-ball! Like Jeremy Snape. It was so, so slow and full - a full toss in fact. It should have ended up out of Adelaide but White didn't pick it up and patted it back to the bowler
Trott is doing a fine all-round job, landing this on a length with no pace at all and it's driven to long-on
dribbles off the thigh and bat onto Prior's gloves and cannons away for a couple. Drop chance, if you're being mean
driven very firmly but to mid-on
this is carefully prodded away
oh dear, White runs outside off stump to try and scoop/paddle this away and misses it completely
this time he reverts to convention but timing has deserted him this innings
another milked single down the ground
finally White times one! Down the wicket and lifting this into a gap wide of deep cover, it sped to the rope
driven firmly back towards the bowler who dives to get a hand on it. Brings up a 50 stand, it took a while
oops, shoved down the leg side and Yardy has to apologise
Hussey does as he's gone all innings and works a single
Yardy sees White coming down the track and fires it in quicker, preventing any runs
ah, lovely shot, White waited on this and thumped to cover, the man on the boundary thought he had a chance but he couldn't catch up with it
Hussey this time is on the charge and slaps this out to deep cover. Well timed enough to take a couple
no getting this away as it's worked to short midwicket
Hussey aims a drive, not an expansive one, so helps himself to a single down the ground
White flings his arms hard at the ball and it trickles down to long-off
Trott does the trick! After taking single after single, Hussey tries to beat long-off, he couldn't and ended up lofting a simple catch
White finishes the over by pushing to cover
full and straight from Tremlett, driven past the bowler for a single
White gets another single by driving towards long on, that asking-rate demands a bit more than singles though
Smith moves forward and punches a length ball through cover, the score ticks over
played off the back foot towards point
a full toss at 139 kph, it was a touch low, and White pushed it tamely towards the off
tight line and length. White stride forward and blocks.
Trott goes past the bat, Smith tried to run it down to third man but couldn't connect
he should have done better with that full toss, instead Smith sliced it straight to the fielder at point, along the ground though
whipped off the pads towards midwicket, good timing, no placement
short ball and Smith gives that a fearful whack, pulling powerfully over midwicket and wide of the fielder in the deep
driven off the front foot with power to the deep cover boundary
played off the pads off the front foot through midwicket
Smith drives firmly at a full ball from Tremlett but can't get past the giant of a bowler
wide outside off stump and Smith throws his bat at the ball, cutting it hard with a flash of his bat, sending it blazing through point
strays down leg side, Tremlett will have to bowl that again
defended on the back foot towards point
Smith opens the face and guides the ball behind point for one, but Smith wants two and he absolutely sprints back for the second. Top running

Smith mis-times the pull and gets hit on the body, the ball goes on the off side and there's no run. Prior runs across and throws needlessly at the stumps at the batsman's end and concedes an overthrow of the rebound
White pulls down to fine leg and smith urges him back for another quick double
full ball outside off, Smith stays in his crease and drills the ball through cover for a single
White frees his arms and thumps the ball towards long off, hit with power but just the two
played towards the leg side on the front foot
hit hard off the back foot towards cover

caught! And that might be it. White decided Trott had to go and muscled a length ball towards long-on. White had to create all the pace because Trott was giving him nothing to work with and he didn't hit it well enough. Yardy ran in from the boundary and held the catch.
Smith works the ball off the pads towards midwicket
played off the back foot towards point
short of a length and the batsman gets on top of the bounce and paddles it towards deep square
played with an open face towards point
full ball angling into the right-hander, played towards midwicket
Hastings was out if Strauss had hit the stumps at the batsman's end from midwicket. He didn't

well Strauss has caught Hastings now! Hastings had moved towards leg to make a bit of room, Anderson followed him with a shorter ball. Hastings was cramped but tried to pull it, the ball hit the top edge and lobbed up towards the leg side. Strauss took a dolly.
another dot ball, that asking-rate is becoming unmanageable now
moves across his stumps to try and swing it towards fine leg. Can't make contact and gets hit on the pad
defended from the crease towards the off side
Lee tries to cut, gets beaten outside off stump
slow and straight from Trott at 117 kph. Lee plays it back to the bowler. Trott reaches out and fields the ball.
this time he connects with the cut and plays it towards third man
Lee nudges the ball awkwardly on the leg side and sets off to the non-striker's end
Smith pushes the ball towards Anderson's left and the bowler dives full length to make the save
Smith also tries to make room to play on the off. Anderson doesn't give it to him and Smith can only push to cover
cut off the back foot towards third man
played from the crease towards cover, Anderson is bowling wicket to wicket on a tight length
too straight this time and Smith flicks the ball to the man on the edge of the circle at midwicket
slower ball to start with, Smith flicks it off his pads and tears back for a second and makes it with a full length dive
Smith jumps out of his crease and makes room, Shahzad beats his attempted hit towards the off side and goes between the batsman and the stumps
slower ball, played towards short third man and they run a single
Lee didn't know too much about that short of a length delivery, it bounced off the high part of the bat and lobbed towards point where it fell short of the fielder
the yorker, beats Smith, and misses leg stump
another one in the blockhole, Smith moves towards leg and drives through cover point
Anderson follows Smith's attempt to make room with a short ball, Smith gets down low and pulls it to deep square leg
Lee swishes, aiming for the leg-side boundary, and misses the short ball
up and over. Lee gets under a short and wide ball and cuts it hard over the off side. It bounces once before going over the point boundary
Lee swings again, aiming for down the ground, but gets an inside edge towards the leg side
full ball in the blockhole and Smith manages to squeeze it towards deep backward square leg with a whip of his bat. Morgan dives on the boundary to save the four
very short, and extremely wide.
and he follows up that wayward delivery with a pinpoint yorker that beats Lee
full toss around thigh height, Smith flicks towards the leg side
Shahzad follows Lee's movement towards the leg side with a full toss, Lee mis-times his shot over the bowler's head.
short and slow, Smith walks across his stumps and paddles the ball towards deep backward square leg
Smith tries to power the ball through the off side but can't beat cover
the slower ball beats Smith's pull and he sets off for a run. Prior runs towards the stumps and then misses the underarm attempt to hit the stumps
full ball outside off, squeezed towards point
the full ball hits the pad outside off stump after Smith failed to hit the ball through leg after moving across
Lee makes room by moving towards leg, Anderson responds with a delivery in the blockhole just outside off, Lee edges it between the keeper and short third man
played towards midwicket for a single
another blockhole delivery, not much Smith can do with that but push it towards the leg side for one
Lee backs away and swings hard at a short ball from Anderson, pulling it flat and fast into the gap between two fielders on the midwicket boundary
fuller ball this time and Lee hits it down the ground for a single
short, slow ball but it's down leg side, Lee swivels and pulls past short fine leg, he hasn't timed it well enough to get four though
that's wide down leg and Prior fumbles it was well. The ball trickles down towards the boundary and the batsmen run three more
Lee tees off against a full ball and smashes it towards deep midwicket. Won't find the boundary though as two fielders close in on it
driven hard along the ground to mid-off
Smith makes a lot of room and cuts but he cannot find the angle to place the ball past the fielder at point
up there in the blockhole, Lee can only play it back to Shahzad
another terrific death-over delivery, Lee can't get under it and drives towards mid-off
short of a length ball and Lee mis-times the slog, the ball falls safely inside the circle near mid-off
Smith slogs across the line and gets one towards midwicket
a slow full toss and Lee cuts it towards third man. Wonder how Razzaq would have treated that one
Lee flat bats another full ball down the ground towards long on
slower short ball, Smith swings hard and misses. Did I hear a groan as he didn't connect with anything?

full ball and Smith blazes it towards deep cover where Morgan sprints to his right and dives to make the save. He ball slips out of his grasp as he is sliding but he keeps his calm to grab it again. Terrific effort and the throw back to Tremlett is top class. Tremlett broke the stumps and that was a close run out call. Why didn't anyone appeal? Smith looks short of his ground
pulled towards midwicket for one more
full ball angling into middle and leg, Smith swings hard and launches the ball flat towards deep square for a one-bounce four
full toss on leg stump, Smith should have hammered that but he failed to make proper contact
yorker. And a terrific one. Lee gets beaten and the ball blazes between stumps and body
Lee swings with all he's got, and he mis-times it. The ball hangs in the air for ages and then falls safely
driven to long on for one
the slower ball and the batsman fails to make contact. they run a bye and Prior misses the run out again
Tremlett's yorker gets squeezed out by Smith, steering it past Prior for four
another one in the blockhole, driven to cover
full and wide outside off stump, Lee was making room and was then too far away from the ball to play a shot
Lee makes room, and flays the ball over extra cover. Four runs but it's all futile now
pulled away towards deep midwicket and England have kept the series alive with a clinical performance at the Adelaide Oval
